SIMPLE: whur
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Whur
<hw>Whur</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Probably of imitative
origin. Cf. <er>Hurr</er>, <er>Hurry</er>, <er>Whir</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To make a rough, humming sound, like one who
pronounces the letter <xex>r</xex> with too much force; to whir; to
birr.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To snarl or growl, as a dog.</def>
<rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whur</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Whur
<hw>Whur</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A humming or whirring
sound, like that of a body moving through the air with velocity; a
whir.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whurry</ent>⟦br⟧
